{
  "texts": [
    "Next, for each spot i, we use a specially structured variational distribution q(z i |c i, x i) that uses cell state proportions to sample the latent variables z i.",
    "Because each spot contains multiple cell states with proportions c i, the structured variational distribution is assumed to decompose as a combination of cell state-specific terms (denoted by ζ(k, x i) for each cell state k), weighted by the proportion of cell states c i.",
    "The variational family factorizes in the form q(u, c, z, l|x",
    "parametrized by new variational parameters m k and v k and neural networks λ, γ and ζ as follows:",
    "In summary, for each cell state k, the function ζ(k, x i) deconvolves the contribution of cell state k to the latent representation of z i."
  ]
}